data.title: Battle of the busiest rockstars
data.meta_description: Compare JACK WHITE vs JOSH HOMME vs DAVE GROHL vs DAMON ALBARN
data.text: Other ProjectsThird Man Records (Label Company), It Might Get Loud (Documentary) OST Soundtracks ( Cold Mountain, Quantum Solace, Shine A Light, Zombieland, The Great Gatsby)Collaborating with artists such as Mondo Generator, Foo Fighters, PJ Harvey, Fatso Jetson, Mark Lanegan Band, Trent Reznor, Masters of Reality, Millionaire, Wellwater Conspiracy, U.N.K.L.E., Primal Scream, Melissa Auf der Maur, Paz Lenchantin, Death from Above 1979, Earthlings, Mastodon, Peaches, The Strokes, Local H, Biffy Clyro, The Prodigy and Arctic Monkeys.Sound City (documentary), Rock star voice cameos for heavy metal parody/tribute show Metalocalypse, temporarily joined Paul McCartney, Cage the Elephant, QOTSA, and many other bands as drummer, Keynote speaker at SXSW 2013. Collaborations with King Buzzo, Mike Watt, The Stinky Puffs, Puff Daddy, earthlings, Tom Petty and the Heartbreakers, MxPx, Tony Iommi, Tenacious D, David Bowie, Cat Power, Killing Joke, The Bangles, Garbage, NIN, Pete Yorn, Juliette and the Licks, Lemmy Kilmister, Slash, Ghost.Backing Vocal for Massive Attack. Soundtrack works: Trainspotting, Ravenous, 101 Reykjavic, Ordinary Decent, Criminal, The Boy in The Oak. Theatre and Opera works: Monkey (Journey to the West), Doctor DeeProducerYes All of White Stripes albums, Soledad Brothers, The Von Bondies, Loretta Lynn, The Muldoons, The Raconteurs, The Dead Weather, Jerry Lee Lewis, Karen Elson, Dan SartainYes Them Crooked Vultures, Arctic Monkeys (Humbug, Suck it and See, AM)Yes King Buzzo, The Foo Fighters, Touch (OST), Into The Pink, Chariots on Fire, CursesYes Bobby Womack
